==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incertum
<hw>In*cer"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Doubtful; not
of definite form.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Opus incertum</b></col> <fld>(Anc. Arch.)</fld>, <cd>a
kind of masonry employed in building walls, in which the stones were not
squared nor laid in courses; rubblework.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incessable</ent>⟦br⟧
